        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: Indian PM met with President Trump just hours after he implemented reciprocal tariffs on foreign countries.</strong></p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Indian PM Narendra Modi met with President Donald Trump, making him the fourth leader to do so in his second term. The meeting focused on trade, defense, energy, and China. Modi <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-02-2025-h1-1-offered-tariff-concessions" target="_blank">offered tariff concessions</a>, business deals, and increased US imports to counter Trump's reciprocal tariffs. The US seeks Indian cooperation on immigration and counterterrorism, positioning India as a key player against China.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;filter:blur(5px);">The talks also touched on Elon Musk’s business interests and intelligence collaboration. The two leaders signed an energy agreement for India to import more US oil. Just before his visit, Trump signed a memorandum directing his advisers to calculate reciprocal tariffs on foreign countries, but he didn't provide many concrete details about the plan.</p>
        </mj-text>
